y` in `f`'s domain with `c = ArchimedeanClass (y - x)`, but there\nis no closer `z` to `x` where the difference is of a higher `ArchimedeanClass`, then\n`f.eval x` is simply `f.val y` truncated at `c`.\n\nThis doesn't mean every `x` can be evaluated this way: it is possible that one can find\nan infinite chain of `y` that keeps getting closer to `x` in terms of Archimedean classes,\nyet `x` is still isolated within a very high Archimedean class. In fact, in the next theorem,\nwe will show that there is always such chain for `x` not in `f`'s domain. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Module/HahnEmbedding.html#HahnEmbedding.Partial.eval_eq_truncLT","kind":"theorem","line":679,"name":"HahnEmbedding.Partial.eval_eq_truncLT","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Module/HahnEmbedding.lean#L679-L702"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Order/Module/HahnEmbedding.html#HahnEmbedding.Partial.eval_ne\"><span class=\"name\">HahnEmbedding</span>.<span class=\"name\">Partial</span>.<span class=\"name\">eval_ne</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#DivisionRing\">DivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/LinearOrder.html#LinearOrder\">LinearOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Or